=== 內蒙古雙語教育爭議 ===
{{Main|2020年內蒙古雙語教育新政策爭議}}
[[中華人民共和國|中國]][[內蒙古自治區教育廳|內蒙古自治區教育廳]]於2020年8月26日發布的小學課程改革方案所引发的争议。本次课程改革要求以[[蒙古語|蒙古語]]授課的[[小學|小學]]（民族學校）的語文科自2020年9月1日起[[中华人民共和国教育部中小学统编教材|改用教育部统编教材]]、[[道德与法治|道德与法治]]科（2016年前稱[[品德与社会|品德与社会]]）在2021年秋[[中华人民共和国教育部中小学统编教材|改用教育部统编教材]]、以上兩科目[[中国地方语言教学|取消地方语言教学]]改以[[中华人民共和国国家通用语言文字法|国家通用语言文字]]（[[普通話|普通話]]）授課。

美國媒體[[洛杉磯時報|洛杉磯時報]]和美國[[哈佛大學|哈佛大學]][[新清史_(學派)|新清史]]學者Mark C. Elliott认为，[[习近平|习近平]]在2012年上任[[中国共产党中央委员会总书记|中共中央总书记]]后，开始摒棄以前蘇聯式的[[蘇聯本土化政策|蘇聯本土化政策]]，改為走类似西方的[[民族大熔爐|民族大熔爐]]政策，尤其是美國式大熔爐，称之为“第二代民族政策”，以期解決中國的民族問題。<ref name="latimes0904">{{cite news|first=Alice|last=Su|title=China cracks down on Inner Mongolian minority fighting for its mother tongue|url=https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2020-09-03/china-inner-mongolia-bilingual-education-assimilation-xinjiang-resistance-crackdown|date=2020-09-04|work=L.A. Times|quote=That changed with Xi, under whom China launched a “second generation” approach to ethnic minorities in recent years. It rejects the old [[蘇聯本土化政策|Soviet-based system]], which allowed relative autonomy and preservation of language and culture in designated regions, in favor of a new “[[民族大熔爐|melting pot]]” approach that emphasizes assimilation into Han Chinese culture.|accessdate=2021-01-22|archive-date=2020-09-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200904125715/https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2020-09-03/china-inner-mongolia-bilingual-education-assimilation-xinjiang-resistance-crackdown|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Baioud">{{cite journal|title=Will education reform wipe out Mongolian language and culture?|first=Gegentuul|last=Baioud|date=2020-08-30|journal=Language on the Move|url=https://www.languageonthemove.com/will-education-reform-wipe-out-mongolian-language-and-culture/|quote=Chinese scholars Ma Rong, Hu Angang and Hu Lianhe, who boldly proposed a Second Generation of Ethnic Policies to solve ethnic “problems” by aggressively assimilating minorities (Leibold 2012). They envisioned the “[[民族大熔爐|melting pot]]” formula of the West, in particular USA, as the ultimate “solution” to the ethnic “problems” of China, even though China’s native minorities are drastically different from diasporic immigrants in America|access-date=2021-01-22|archive-date=2020-09-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200903160643/https://www.languageonthemove.com/will-education-reform-wipe-out-mongolian-language-and-culture/|dead-url=no}} （這段話是總結了以下學者的觀點：Elliott, Mark C. 2015. The Case of the Missing Indigene: Debate Over a “Second-Generation” Ethnic Policy. ''The China Journal'' (73): 186-213,308. ）</ref>

